Hi all,

I am having super fun time trying to turn on mod_dav on an httpd v2.4.53-11.el9 (as shipped by RHEL9).

The request “MKCOL /storage/foo” returns a 201, but doesn't actually do anything. The “foo” directory is silently not created.

Stepping through the code, the code that creates the directory is creating the parent directory “/storage”, and not the actual directory in the request "/storage/foo”:

1137	    status = apr_dir_make(ctx->pathname, APR_OS_DEFAULT, ctx->pool);
(gdb) print ctx->pathname
$6 = 0x7fffbc013450 "/var/www/dav/storage"

This explains the “it’s doing nothing” - it created the parent directory, which already exists.

Looking at the whole request, it looks like the PATH_INFO mechanism hasn't done anything:

